{"title_page": "Network18 Group", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=June 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Network18 Media & Investments Limited\n| image = \n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{Unbulleted list|{{BSE|532798}}|{{NSE|Network18}}}}\n| industry = [[Mass media]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|1993}}\n| location = [[Mumbai|Mumbai, Maharashtra, India]]\n| key_people = Rahul Joshi (managing director)\n| products = {{Unbulleted list|[[Broadcasting]]|[[Publishing]]|[[Film]]|[[Entertainment]]|[[Web portal]]s}}\n| revenue = {{INRConvert|5116|c}} (2019)<ref name=nw18Q4>[http://www.nw18.com/reports/reports/Financial%20Results/2018-19/NW18InvestorsUpdate_Network18_Q4FY19.pdf Network18 Fourth Quatar Results], LiveMint (May 30, 2019)</ref>\n| net_income = {{INRConvert|-303|c}} (2019)<ref name=nw18Q4/> \n| num_employees = 3,000<ref name=nw182019/>\n| parent = Independent Media Trust\n| owner = [[Reliance Industries Ltd.]]\n| divisions = {{Unbulleted list|[[TV18]]|[[Viacom 18]] ([[Joint venture|JV]] of [[ViacomCBS]] and [[TV18]]) (51%)<ref>[https://www.rapidtvnews.com/2011061512860/corporate-restructure-complete-for-indias-network18.html#axzz5EQy6vRPn Corporate restructure complete for India\u2019s Network18]</ref>}} \n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.network18online.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Network18 Media & Investments Limited''', informally referred to as the ''' BnD Network18 Group''', is an [[Media of India|Indian media]] and entertainment group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=30445840|title=Network18 Media & Investments Limited: Private Company Information|last=|first=|authorlink=S&P Global Market Intelligence|date=|website=Bloomberg|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The group was founded and majority owned by [[Raghav Bahl]] in 1993, after [[India]] [[Economic liberalisation in India|liberalised its economy]] and media ownership laws in early 1990s. In the 2000s, the Group grew into one of the largest collection of media properties in [[India]] through debt financing and international licensing deals with global media brands.<ref name=mishraJune2014>[https://www.livemint.com/Companies/rqT2Oi8fwv4XVjJcHzlcVN/Inside-the-Network18-takeover.html Inside the Network18 takeover], Ashish Mishra, LiveMint (The Hindustan Times Gp), (25 Jun 2014)</ref><ref name=forbes05302019/> By late 2011, according to a ''[[LiveMint]]'' article, the Network18 group had amassed a large debt, was running in loss and banks were unwilling to lend the group additional capital.<ref name=mishraJune2014/> Bahl's Network18 group sought capital from the [[Reliance Industries Ltd]] in 2012, then closed loss-making ventures, laid off employees, and trimmed the size of the Group over the next two years. On May 29, 2014, under the terms of its 2012 financing, the Reliance Industries Limited group took over the Network18 empire to integrate it with its 4G, Jio wireless content-distribution strategy.<ref name=mishraJune2014/><ref name=forbes05302019/><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.financialexpress.com/archive/-my-dream-to-own-a-newspaper-is-dead-/1294286/0/ | title=My dream to own a newspaper is dead | date=30 September 2014 | newspaper=Financial Express | accessdate=21 October 2018 }}</ref><ref>[https://www.livemint.com/Companies/Vpo4RrEprzzsFI7xGJw3OP/RIL-to-acquire-control-of-Network-18-spend-Rs4000-crore.html Exits galore as RIL takes over Network18], LiveMint (May 30, 2019)</ref> The Group's leadership team is headed by chairperson Adil Zainulbhai and managing director Rahul Joshi in 2019.<ref name=nw182019>[http://www.nw18.com/reports/reports/Financial%20Results/Annual%20Reports/Network18-Annual%20Report.pdf Group Annual Report: 2018], Network18 Group, SEBI filings (2019), pages 2-4, 61 for current data; [http://www.nw18.com/corporate-main#compHist Network18 Group], About Us, Board and Management Team (May 15, 2019)</ref>\n\nAt its peak, the Network18 Group has included media and internet-based media outlets such as in.com, IBNlive.com, [[Moneycontrol]].com, [[Firstpost]].com, Cricketnext, [[Home Shop 18|Homeshop18]], bookmyshow.com, print magazines such as ''[[Forbes India]]'' and ''Overdrive'', TV channels such as Colors and some in partnership with international media groups such as [[NBC]], [[CNN]], IBN7, [[MTV]], [[Nickelodeon]], and [[CNBC]].<ref name=mishraJune2014/><ref name=forbes05302019>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/meghabahree/2014/05/30/reliance-takes-over-network18-is-this-the-death-of-media-independence/#1aa2c42865c1 Reliance Takes Over Network18: Is This The Death Of Media Independence?], Forbes, Megha Bahree (May 30, 2019)</ref> According to Network18 Group's 2018 annual report, it had 70 [[crore]] (700 million) viewers, employed 1,200 journalists for sourcing content, 3,000 employees on its payroll, and 20 television channels in 15 [[Languages of India|Indian languages]].<ref name=nw182019/>\n\n== History ==\nThe company was incorporated as a [[Private limited company|private limited]] company on 16 February 1996.{{Citation needed|date=May 2018}} In April 2006, the name was changed from SGA Finance and Management Services Private Limited to Network18 Fincap Private Limited and subsequently in November 2006, it was converted into a [[Public limited company|Public Limited]] company. Network18 got listed on the [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] and the [[National Stock Exchange of India|National Stock Exchange]] on 2 February 2007. The shares of the company of face value of \u20b95 each opened at \u20b9312.10 at the [[National Stock Exchange of India|NSE]] and at \u20b9300 at the [[Bombay Stock Exchange|BSE]]. The same year in December, its name was changed from Network18 Fincap Limited to Network18 Media & Investments Limited.{{Citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n\nThe Network 18 Group announced a restructuring plan to create a two listed entity structure for the group in July 2010. The restructuring became effective on 10 June 2011 with the approval of the [[Delhi High Court]] and the group successfully completed the re-alignment of its business operation into 2 sections \u2013 Network18 and TV18. Network18 undertakes the digital and publishing side of the business and TV18 contains the television assets of the group.<ref>{{cite web|title=Restructure complete for Network 18|url=http://www.rapidtvnews.com/index.php/2011061512860/corporate-restructure-complete-for-indias-network18.html|publisher=rapidtvnews.com|accessdate=10 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn Jan 2012, there was a large investment by [[Mukesh Ambani]]'s [[Reliance Industries Limited]] in a complex deal that offered a possibility that Ambani-held Independent Media Trust (IMT) might eventually gain a controlling interest.<ref>\n{{cite news\n | title =        RIL deal-Network18: Is Mukesh Ambani the new media mogul?\n | author =       Sandeep Bamzai\n | publisher =    [[India Today]]\n | url =          http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/bailout-for-raghav-bahl-network-18-signals-mukesh-ambani-willing-to-bet-big-money-on-media/1/168680.html\n | date =         14 January 2012\n}}Quote: \nthe instrumentality ... is an optionally\nconvertible debenture which has every possibility of turning into\nequity. Analysts say that going forward, Ambani will turn into a majority\nstake-holder of Network 18 and TV18 through this mechanism.\n\nOn 29 May 2014, [[Mukesh Ambani]] owned [[Reliance industries]], purchased the company for a reported Rs. 40&nbsp;billion\n</ref> In July 2014, the ownership was transferred to Independent Media Trust. On 29 May 2014, [[Reliance Industries Ltd]] (RIL) announced it would be acquiring control in Network 18 Media & Investments Ltd, including its subsidiary TV18 Broadcast Ltd. The board of RIL approved funding of up to \u20b94,000 [[crore]] (40&nbsp;billion) to Independent Media Trust (IMT), of which RIL is the sole beneficiary, for acquisition of control in Network 18 and its subsidiaries.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/business-news/reliance-industries-ltd-to-acquire-control-of-network-18-to-spend-rs-4-000-crore/article1-1224198.aspx|title=RIL to acquire control of Network 18, Rajdeep may go|publisher= HT Media Limited|accessdate=29 May 2014}}</ref>  On 8 July 2014, RIL stated that it has completed the Network18 take-over.<ref>{{cite news|title=RIL completes Network 18 takeover|url=http://www.patrika.com/news/ril-completes-network-18-takeover/1016660|accessdate=9 July 2014|work=Patrika Group|date=8 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015 Network 18 under ownership of [[Reliance Industries Limited|Reliance Industries]] took over [[ETV Network]] for about {{INR}}2,053 [[crore]] deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/media/network18-finishes-rs-2053-cr-deal-to-acquire-etv-stakes/articleshow/29215772.cms|title=Network18 finishes Rs 2,053-cr deal to acquire ETV stakes|date=10 February 2018|publisher=|via=The Economic Times}}</ref>\n\n== TV 18 ==\nTV18 Broadcast Limited is the broadcasting arm of Network18. TV18 operates India's largest selection of News channels across 15 language and 26 states; with channels like CNBC-TV18, CNBC Awaaz in Business News and CNN News18, News18 India in General News. Through its JV Viacom18, it also operates a number of entertainment channels across genres, including leading premium local channels like Colors, [[Nickelodeon (Indian TV channel)|Nickelodeon]] and MTV. A subsidiary of TV18, the network operates a selection of 13 regional news channels under the News18 brand name. TV18 also operates a joint venture with the Lokmat Group which houses the [[Marathi people|Marathi]] news channel News18 Lokmat. To cover the global audience & sizable [[Non-resident Indian and person of Indian origin|NRI]] population, TV18 operates News18, a twenty-four hour television news channel designed to give the world largest democracy, the latest news.\n\n===Television channels===\nNetwork 18 operates the following channels.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:middle;\n!background:Orange;\"|Category\n!background:Yellow;\"|Sub-Categories\n!background:Orange;\"|Channel\n!background:Yellow;\"|Language\n!background:Orange;\"|Region\n|-\n| rowspan=\"23\" |\n'''News Channels(20)'''\n| rowspan=\"4\" |'''Business News Channels(4)'''\n<br />\n| [[CNBC TV18]] || rowspan=\"2\" |[[English language|English]]|| rowspan=\"3\" | [[India]]\n|-\n| [[CNBC TV18|CNBC TV18 Prime HD]]\n|-\n| [[CNBC Awaaz]] ||[[Hindi]]\n|-\n|  CNBC Bajar ||[[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]||[[Gujarat|Gujarat, India]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''General News Channels(2)'''\n| [[CNN-News18|CNN News18]] ||English || rowspan=\"2\" |[[India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 India]] ||Hindi\n|-\n| rowspan=\"14\" |'''Regional News Channels(14)'''\n| [[News18 Lokmat]] ||[[Marathi language|Marathi]] ||[[Maharashtra|Maharashtra, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Urdu]] ||[[Urdu language|Urdu]] ||[[India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Rajasthan]] ||[[Rajasthani language|Rajasthani]],  Hindi||[[Rajasthan|Rajasthan, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Uttar Pradesh Uttarakhand]] || rowspan=\"3\" |Hindi || [[Uttar Pradesh]] & [[Uttarakhand|Uttarakhand, India]]\n|-\n| News18 Madhya Pradesh Chhattisgarh ||[[Madhya Pradesh]] & [[Chhattisgarh|Chhattisgarh, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Bihar-Jharkhand]] ||[[Bihar]] & [[Jharkhand|Jharkhand, India]]\n|-\n|  News18 Gujarati || [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]||[[Gujarat|Gujarat, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Bangla]] ||[[Bengali language|Bengali]]||[[West Bengal|West Bengal, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Odia]]||[[Odia language|Odia]]||[[Odisha|Odisha, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Kannada]] ||[[Kannada]] ||[[Karnataka|Karnataka, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Kerala]]||[[Malayalam]]||[[Kerala|Kerala, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Tamil Nadu]] ||[[Tamil language|Tamil]]||[[Tamil Nadu|Tamil Nadu, India]]\n|-\n| [[News18 Assam/North-East]] ||[[Assamese language|Assamese]],  English ||[[Assam|Assam, India]]\n|-\n|  News18 Punjab-Har